				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 19 Aug 2017 21:03:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Chubert</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>502908</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Besides the other things that are working in this article which other people pointed out, this works really well for me because it uses a few strategies that I haven't seen that much nowadays. The article is actually pretty narrative-light, relying primarily on the absurdity of the original anomaly to hook you in and finishing with the horror of the final log&#8212;both of these are image-heavy approaches. I also like the approach of taking something everyday and ordinary (KFC and evangelical Christianity) and corrupting it, as opposed to going total fantastical horror; it might just be me, but I haven't seen much of that nowadays. Easy +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
